              "topic_id": "topic-race-conditions",
              "topic_name": "Race Conditions",
              "sort_order": 1,
              "created_at": "2026-03-09T12:00:00Z",
              "updated_at": "2026-03-09T12:00:00Z",
              "questions": [
                {
                  "question_id": "q-race-001",
                  "question_type": "single_best",
                  "title": "Race condition definition",
                  "difficulty": 2,
                  "stem_rich_text": "<p>Which statement best describes a <strong>race condition</strong>?</p>",
                  "main_explanation_rich_text": "<p>A race condition occurs when program behavior depends on the timing or ordering of concurrent operations on shared state.</p>",
                  "reference_text": "Lecture notes: concurrency fundamentals",
                  "created_at": "2026-03-09T12:00:00Z",
                  "updated_at": "2026-03-09T12:00:00Z",
                  "last_edited_at": "2026-03-09T12:00:00Z",
                  "is_bookmarked": false,
                  "is_flagged": false,
                  "choices": [
                    {
                      "choice_id": "q-race-001-a",
                      "label": "A",
                      "choice_rich_text": "<p>A race condition occurs when two threads execute in parallel, regardless of shared memory.</p>",
                      "is_correct": false,
                      "choice_explanation_rich_text": "<p>Parallel execution alone is not enough. Shared state and timing-sensitive behavior are the real issue.</p>",
                      "sort_order": 1
                    },
                    {
                      "choice_id": "q-race-001-b",
                      "label": "B",
                      "choice_rich_text": "<p>A race condition occurs when program output depends on the non-deterministic ordering of concurrent access to shared state.</p>",
                      "is_correct": true,
                      "choice_explanation_rich_text": "<p>This is the best definition.</p>",
                      "sort_order": 2
                    },
                    {
                      "choice_id": "q-race-001-c",
                      "label": "C",
                      "choice_rich_text": "<p>A race condition occurs only when a deadlock happens.</p>",
                      "is_correct": false,
                      "choice_explanation_rich_text": "<p>Deadlock and race conditions are different failure modes.</p>",
                      "sort_order": 3
                    },
                    {
                      "choice_id": "q-race-001-d",
                      "label": "D",
                      "choice_rich_text": "<p>A race condition occurs only in distributed systems.</p>",
                      "is_correct": false,
                      "choice_explanation_rich_text": "<p>They also occur in multi-threaded local programs.</p>",
                      "sort_order": 4
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "question_id": "q-race-002",
                  "question_type": "multi_select",
                  "title": "Ways to reduce race conditions",
                  "difficulty": 3,
                  "stem_rich_text": "<p>Which of the following techniques can reduce or eliminate race conditions? Select all that apply.</p>",
                  "main_explanation_rich_text": "<p>Synchronization and reducing shared mutable state are common strategies.</p>",
                  "reference_text": "Lecture notes: locks and synchronization",
                  "created_at": "2026-03-09T12:00:00Z",
                  "updated_at": "2026-03-09T12:00:00Z",
                  "last_edited_at": "2026-03-09T12:00:00Z",
                  "is_bookmarked": true,
                  "is_flagged": false,
                  "choices": [
                    {
                      "choice_id": "q-race-002-a",
                      "label": "A",
                      "choice_rich_text": "<p>Use mutexes around critical sections.</p>",
                      "is_correct": true,
                      "choice_explanation_rich_text": "<p>Mutexes protect shared state by controlling access.</p>",
                      "sort_order": 1
                    },
                    {
                      "choice_id": "q-race-002-b",
                      "label": "B",
                      "choice_rich_text": "<p>Use immutable data where practical.</p>",
                      "is_correct": true,
                      "choice_explanation_rich_text": "<p>Immutable data reduces shared mutable state bugs.</p>",
                      "sort_order": 2
                    },
                    {
                      "choice_id": "q-race-002-c",
                      "label": "C",
                      "choice_rich_text": "<p>Increase CPU clock speed.</p>",
                      "is_correct": false,
                      "choice_explanation_rich_text": "<p>That does not solve synchronization issues.</p>",
                      "sort_order": 3
                    },
                    {
                      "choice_id": "q-race-002-d",
                      "label": "D",
                      "choice_rich_text": "<p>Use atomic operations where appropriate.</p>",
                      "is_correct": true,
                      "choice_explanation_rich_text": "<p>Atomic operations can eliminate some races on shared variables.</p>",
                      "sort_order": 4
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "question_id": "q-race-003",
                  "question_type": "short_answer",
                  "title": "Critical section meaning",
                  "difficulty": 2,
                  "stem_rich_text": "<p>Define a <strong>critical section</strong> in concurrent programming.</p>",
                  "model_answer_rich_text": "<p>A critical section is a portion of code that accesses shared state and must not be executed by more than one thread or process at the same time.</p>",
                  "main_explanation_rich_text": "<p>The key idea is mutually exclusive access to shared resources.</p>",
                  "reference_text": "Lecture notes: critical sections",
                  "created_at": "2026-03-09T12:00:00Z",
                  "updated_at": "2026-03-09T12:00:00Z",
                  "last_edited_at": "2026-03-09T12:00:00Z",
                  "is_bookmarked": false,
                  "is_flagged": false
                }
              ],
              "flashcards": [
                {
                  "flashcard_id": "fc-race-001",
                  "front_rich_text": "<p>What is a race condition?</p>",
                  "back_rich_text": "<p>A bug where behavior depends on the timing/order of concurrent accesses to shared state.</p>",
                  "reference_text": "Lecture notes: concurrency fundamentals",
                  "created_at": "2026-03-09T12:00:00Z",
